folder: Franklin Avenue & Sterling Place, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Franklin Avenue, at the northeast corner of Sterling street, showing several old homes. E. Armbruster states that the one-story house on the right was known as the Point Lot Grocery.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
1922

folder: Sterling Place & Franklin Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Sterling Place, west from Franklin Avenue, showing the north side of the street. In the distance is St. Theresa's Roman Catholic Church at Classon Avenue.

View 2 shows the north side of the street from Classon Avenue.

P. L. Sperr
September 6, 1941.
Views 1, 2
